{:component/id :orbiplex/temporal-storage-convention
 :component/title "Temporal Storage Convention"
 :component/type :architecture-convention
 :component/status :accepted

 :summary
 "Solution-level storage convention for SQLite-backed Node stores: append
 transaction/event facts, derive current projections with as_of_tx_id, and prove
 replay equivalence in tests."

 :must-implement
 [{:cap/id :temporal-event-log-shape
   :title "Temporal Event Log Shape"
   :kind :storage-contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/062-temporal-storage-convention.md"]
   :schemas []
   :responsibilities
   ["Represent local writes as transaction rows plus event rows"
    "Keep actor, causation, correlation, and signature metadata on transactions"
    "Use idempotency_key for logical request deduplication at the event boundary"
    "Use valid_from and valid_until only for domains with real valid-time semantics"]
   :status :done}

  {:cap/id :derived-current-projection
   :title "Derived Current Projection"
   :kind :storage-contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/062-temporal-storage-convention.md"]
   :schemas []
   :responsibilities
   ["Serve API and UI reads from current projection tables"
    "Treat the event log as the recovery source of truth"
    "Carry as_of_tx_id on projection rows instead of updated_at"
    "Keep optimistic-concurrency version as derived projection state"]
   :status :done}

  {:cap/id :replay-equivalence-testing
   :title "Replay Equivalence Testing"
   :kind :test-contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/062-temporal-storage-convention.md"]
   :schemas []
   :responsibilities
   ["Prove that projection replay from events equals the live projection"
    "Cover as-of replay before and after representative state transitions"
    "Cover bootstrap migration from pre-temporal current rows"
    "Cover privacy invariants for event payloads"]
   :status :done}

  {:cap/id :per-store-performance-profile
   :title "Per-Store Performance Profile"
   :kind :storage-operations-contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/062-temporal-storage-convention.md"]
   :schemas []
   :responsibilities
   ["Select minimal, balanced, or full-audit retention profile per store"
    "Use neutral DeviceFootprint defaults rather than daemon deployment-class semantics in lower storage layers"
    "Require explicit operator acknowledgement for full-audit on non-critical device footprints"
    "Keep one schema per store kind and make indices/expensive queries profile-aware"
    "Apply profile-specific busy timeout and expose retention, compaction, lease, checksum, and power dimensions"
    "Treat cross-store correlation queries as partial when shorter-retention stores have compacted history"]
   :status :done}

  {:cap/id :temporal-compaction-and-manifest
   :title "Temporal Compaction and Storage Manifest"
   :kind :storage-operations-contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/062-temporal-storage-convention.md"]
   :schemas []
   :responsibilities
   ["Provide shared compaction decision calculation according to the store profile"
    "Run age-based planned compaction according to the store profile"
    "Run emergency disk-pressure compaction before writes fail"
    "Emit operator notification and best-effort state-changed signal for emergency compaction when temporal history is actually reclaimed"
    "Write a store manifest listing profile, acknowledged disk cost, files, size, and as-of tx id for backup and operator UI"]
   :status :done}]

 :may-implement
 [{:cap/id :shared-temporal-helper-crate
   :title "Shared Temporal Helper Crate"
   :kind :optional
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/062-temporal-storage-convention.md"]
   :schemas []
   :responsibilities
   ["Extract typed TxId/EventId and replay harness helpers only after at least two stores converge"
    "Avoid creating a database framework before the shape is proven by pilots"]
   :status :deferred}]

 :out-of-scope
 ["Replacing domain-specific validation and projection logic"
  "Providing distributed transactions across stores"
  "Turning JSONL audit mirrors into the canonical temporal store"]

 :consumes []
 :produces []

:notes
 ["Notification store is the first implemented core temporal event-log/projection pilot and first performance-profile adopter."
  "Node now has temporal-profile, device-power with macOS/Linux best-effort detection, storage-manifest with temporal markers, profile-aware bounded worker passes, daemon performance config, notification-store profile-driven SQLite pragmas, profile-aware notification indices, notification manifests, destructive notification-store compaction for minimal/balanced, and startup emergency disk-pressure compaction notification plus best-effort state-changed signal when history is reclaimed."
  "Messaging outbox status/attempt storage and Seed Directory accepted facts are converged bounded/no-op adopters: both expose temporal status/feed/replay-check and storage manifests while reporting compaction.policy = bounded-noop with domain retention rationale."
  "The hard-MVP compaction boundary is explicit: notification-store is full-compaction-required; messaging and Seed Directory accepted facts are bounded-noop-required."
  "Shared temporal replay helpers remain optional because the current shared crate deliberately stops at mechanical event/replay primitives."
  "The shared temporal-event-log crate remains intentionally mechanical and does not own domain retention, redaction, attempts, or destructive compaction semantics."]}
